    ],
    "solution": "$\\left[\\operatorname{Pt}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_2 \\mathrm{Br}_2\\right]$\n<br><br>Hybridisation : dsp${ }^2$, geometry : square planar\n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1liw92juu/ec23a91b-a09a-40e9-8d6a-38da20cd756b/10adca60-0afe-11ee-8e6d-ed93ab6ac878/file-6y3zli1liw92juv.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1liw92juu/ec23a91b-a09a-40e9-8d6a-38da20cd756b/10adca60-0afe-11ee-8e6d-ed93ab6ac878/file-6y3zli1liw92juv.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2023 Paper 2 Online Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 15 English Explanation 1\">\n<br>(A) $\\left[\\mathrm{Pt}(\\mathrm{en})(\\mathrm{SCN})_2\\right]$ : square planar, cis-trans not possible\n<br><br>(B) $\\left[\\mathrm{Zn}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_2 \\mathrm{Cl}_2\\right]$ : tetrahedral, cis-trans not possible\n<br><br>(C) $\\left[\\operatorname{Pt}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_3\\right)_2 \\mathrm{Cl}_4\\right]$ : octahedral, cis-trans possible\n<br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1liw94z8g/fb63c934-93b1-4a4b-b418-73a769f83fa3/542d2600-0afe-11ee-8e6d-ed93ab6ac878/file-6y3zli1liw94z8h.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1liw94z8g/fb63c934-93b1-4a4b-b418-73a769f83fa3/542d2600-0afe-11ee-8e6d-ed93ab6ac878/file-6y3zli1liw94z8h.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2023 Paper 2 Online Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 15 English Explanation 2\">\n<br>$$\n\\text { (D) }\\left[\\mathrm{Cr}(\\mathrm{en})_2\\left(\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}\\right) \\mathrm{SO}_4\\right]^{+} \\text {: Octahedral }\n$$\n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1liw97e3z/8d68b4d9-1f47-4840-888f-0549f4b26362/97492bf0-0afe-11ee-8e6d-ed93ab6ac878/file-6y3zli1liw97e40.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1liw97e3z/8d68b4d9-1f47-4840-888f-0549f4b26362/97492bf0-0afe-11ee-8e6d-ed93ab6ac878/file-6y3zli1liw97e40.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2023 Paper 2 Online Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 15 English Explanation 3\">",
