    "solution": "The given complex [Pt(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>Cl<sub>2</sub>]Br<sub>2</sub> has three ionisation isomers and each of them has two geometrical isomers.\n<br><br>Three ionisation isomers are\n<br>(i) [Pt(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>Cl<sub>2</sub>]Br<sub>2</sub> \n<br>(ii) [Pt(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>ClBr]BrCl\n<br>(iii) [Pt(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>Br<sub>2</sub>]Cl\n<p>Ionisation isomers are compounds having same molecular\nformula but have different counter ions.</p>\n<p>Each isomer shown above also possess two more geometrical\nisomers. Geometrical isomers are the compounds having\ndifferent arrangement of atoms in space but same molecular\nformula.</p>\n<p>The geometrical isomers are :</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kx79a8mh/b2709f6a-f3be-4a89-b194-4042e6e2ea68/c3487190-5d7e-11ec-8979-a142bee06a98/file-1kx79a8mi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kx79a8mh/b2709f6a-f3be-4a89-b194-4042e6e2ea68/c3487190-5d7e-11ec-8979-a142bee06a98/file-1kx79a8mi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2021 Paper 1 Online Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 44 English Explanation\">",
    "__v": 0,
    "title": "JEE Advanced 2021 Paper 1 Online"
  },
