    "tags": [],
    "options": [
      "It has two geometrical isomers",
      "It will have three geometrical isomers if bidentate 'en' is replaced by two cyanide ligands ",
      "It is paramagnetic ",
      "It absorbs light at longer wavelength as compared to \n<br><br>$${\\left[ {Co\\left( {en} \\right){{\\left( {N{H_3}} \\right)}_4}} \\right]^{3 + }}$$ "
    ],
    "solution": "<p>Option (A) : Correct. The complex [Co(en)(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>3</sub>(H<sub>2</sub>O)]<sup>3+</sup> has two following isomers:</p>\n<p> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kywp3axv/f70ef7a4-c0a1-40a3-b43a-d713b8eeffb7/6416c730-7f48-11ec-9a1e-9f87431102fd/file-1kywp3axw.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kywp3axv/f70ef7a4-c0a1-40a3-b43a-d713b8eeffb7/6416c730-7f48-11ec-9a1e-9f87431102fd/file-1kywp3axw.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 53 English Explanation 1\"> </p>\n<p>Option (B) : Correct. When bidentate 'en' is replaced by two cyanide ligands complex [Co(CN)<sub>2</sub>(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>3</sub>(H<sub>2</sub>O)]<sup>+</sup> will have three following isomers:</p>\n<p> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kywp3tn0/fdd95d4e-3427-4021-b888-fdc13b86e5af/728870c0-7f48-11ec-9a1e-9f87431102fd/file-1kywp3tn1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kywp3tn0/fdd95d4e-3427-4021-b888-fdc13b86e5af/728870c0-7f48-11ec-9a1e-9f87431102fd/file-1kywp3tn1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 53 English Explanation 2\"> </p>\n<p>Option (C) : Incorrect. Incomplex [Co(en)(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>3</sub>(H<sub>2</sub>O)]<sup>3+</sup>, Co is in + 3 oxidation, that is, [Ar]d<sup>6</sup>. In the presence given ligands the complex will have low spin, hence, diamagnetic.</p>\n<p>Option (D) : Correct. In complex [Co(en)(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>]<sup>3+</sup> there is larger gap between t<sub>2g</sub> and e<sub>g</sub> than in complex [Co(en)(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>3</sub>(H<sub>2</sub>O)]<sup>3+</sup>. Hence [Co(en)(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>3</sub>(H<sub>2</sub>O)]<sup>3+</sup> will absorb light at longer wavelength as compared to [Co(en)(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>]<sup>3+</sup>.</p>",
    "__v": 0,
    "title": "JEE Advanced 2018 Paper 2 Offline"
  },
