    "options": [
      "P-4, Q-2, R-3, S-1",
      "P-3, Q-1, R-4, S-2",
      "P-2, Q-1, R-3, S-4",
      "P-1, Q-3, R-4, S-2"
    ],
    "solution": "<p>For [Cr(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>Cl<sub>2</sub>]Cl,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l198k2jr/8019ca22-b341-420c-9637-2162f155fd82/5a5dcf70-adc6-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l198k2js.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l198k2jr/8019ca22-b341-420c-9637-2162f155fd82/5a5dcf70-adc6-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l198k2js.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 38 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>For [Ti(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>5</sub>Cl](NO<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>,</p>\n<p> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l198xs02/401f2ac9-7ada-4d55-bd34-c5659579a087/d78c0e20-adc7-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l198xs03.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l198xs02/401f2ac9-7ada-4d55-bd34-c5659579a087/d78c0e20-adc7-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l198xs03.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 38 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>The complex is paramagnetic due to presence of unpaired electron.</p>\n<p>Since the groups between the complex ion and ions outside can be exchanged, it shows ionisation isomerism.</p>\n<p>For [Pt(en)(NH<sub>3</sub>)Cl]NO<sub>3</sub>,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l198z824/a2f81857-bff3-42fe-8ad2-4a668509e0c0/ffc28cc0-adc7-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l198z825.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l198z824/a2f81857-bff3-42fe-8ad2-4a668509e0c0/ffc28cc0-adc7-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l198z825.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 38 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p>The complex is square planar and all electrons are paired. So it is diamagnetic. Since the groups between the complex ion and ions outside can be exchanged, it shows ionisation isomerism.</p>\n<p>For [Co(NH<sub>3</sub>)<sub>4</sub>(NO<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>]NO<sub>3</sub>, NH<sub>3</sub> is a strong ligand and causes pairing</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l19908l0/5e5a74c1-655b-44c2-a074-375a6e547119/1bf99a50-adc8-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l19908l1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l19908l0/5e5a74c1-655b-44c2-a074-375a6e547119/1bf99a50-adc8-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l19908l1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 38 English Explanation 4\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1992ssd/357699a9-2073-4067-8bd7-2798ec4e85b9/633365e0-adc8-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l1992sse.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1992ssd/357699a9-2073-4067-8bd7-2798ec4e85b9/633365e0-adc8-11ec-87cf-6f66ef86ef1e/file-1l1992sse.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Advanced 2014 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 38 English Explanation 5\"></p>",
