    "solution": "<p>For a complex to be optically active, it should not possess either centre of symmetry or axis of symmetry or plane of symmetry. Here, the given complex is an octahedral complex that possesses plane of symmetry as well as axis of symmetry and thus is optically inactive.</p>\n<p>The $$cis$$ and $$trans$$ both form of complex [M(NH$$_3$$)$$_4$$Cl$$_2$$] are optically inactive.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lgewql96/c590dee3-c5bb-48bc-8eb7-40676bd62c3e/14b397a0-d9dc-11ed-af1f-bf7b0ee7d77a/file-1lgewql97.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lgewql96/c590dee3-c5bb-48bc-8eb7-40676bd62c3e/14b397a0-d9dc-11ed-af1f-bf7b0ee7d77a/file-1lgewql97.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2008 Paper 2 Offline Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 23 English Explanation\"></p>",
